## Project Structure

```
[[.ServiceName]]/
├── cmd/http/main.go        ← entry point, graceful lifecycle
├── config/                 ← YAML config files
├── internal/
│   ├── config/             ← Viper config loader
│   ├── core/               ← wires all dependencies
│   ├── deliveries/http/    ← handlers, middleware, router
│   ├── models/             ← domain models + DTOs
│   ├── pkg/                ← shared utilities
│   ├── repository/         ← data access layer
│   └── service/            ← business logic
├── migration/              ← SQL migration files
├── builds/Dockerfile
└── docker-compose.yml
```

## Getting Started

1. Copy and edit environment config:
   ```bash
   cp config/config.local.example.yaml config/config.local.yaml
   # Edit config.local.yaml with your credentials
   ```

2. Start infrastructure:
   ```bash
   docker compose up -d
   ```

3. Run the app:
   ```bash
   make run
   ```

4. Health check:
   ```
   GET http://localhost:8080/health
   ```
[[- if .UseSwagger]]

5. API docs:
   ```
   GET http://localhost:8080/swagger/index.html
   ```
[[- end]]

